pr_review_body:
@vineetvermait  could you please correct the failing checks and squash your commits so it is one commit. 

@rht Can you please give it a second look

Then it should be good to merge

@gshuflin already added support for the return types of rules to indicate that they are failures, and thus uncacheable. It's used for thing right now: marking processes with non-zero exit codes uncacheable. https://github.com/pantsbuild/pants/blob/9501b3c456b8be6557c919aac44c691703a07d15/src/rust/engine/src/nodes.rs#L1383-L1399

This change should probably use that facility + a flag on the engine-aware return type that indicates that the result was a failure.

The actual mechanism here is small, so I'm fine with landing this temporarily though. Would be good to follow up to use the existing mechanism, which will be less error prone for further error types.

@AsafYagoda, thank you very much for your contribution.
I submitted few comments, could You please have a look, if they make sense ?
Please add yourself also to AUTHORS.txt and authors.rst files.

This looks good to me. 

We probably shouldn't be modifying the state of `ctypeslib` on line 97, but that can wait for a future PR.

@vasily-v-ryabov Would you like to take a look before this gets merged? I am unable to test it.
